mpb27:
A merge will also cause a stack overflow regardless of SkipConstructor.
``` C#
            // ... create a non-default Foo (with BarB) ...
            var fooWithBarB = new Foo() { SomeBar = new BarB() { Value = 321.0 } };
        // ... serialize it into memory ...
        var ms = new MemoryStream();
        Serializer.Serialize<Foo>(ms, fooWithBarB);

        // ... create an instance of Foo to merge with ...
        var mergeFoo = new Foo();

        // ... merge which will cause a buffer overflow ...
        ms.Position = 0;
        Serializer.Merge<Foo>(ms, mergeFoo);

```
