This method can partial solve my problem. In my project i can control the startup.
However some of library projects will provide to others use.
In some document about Protobuf 3, have two solution for Inheritace: one is use oneof equals to ProtoInclude and the other is "Composite" define a property with type is base class.
If use ProtoInclude there a two little flaw
1.  When add or remove a child class, you should modify base class.
2. Consider about byte size of field number, use which number as the first ProtoInclude argument sometimes becomes a question.
Since if use a small number when need to add filed to base class the property field number will greater than child class field number, and then add a child class, the child class field number will greater than some property field number, I think it's a little problem.
But if use a great enough number will west of memory and network bandwidth.
Considering these problem, I prefer to add a ProtoInheritAttribute, in .net one class only have one base class just set the base class field number to 1.
How do you think?. I've try to solved this case, and create a pull request
https://github.com/mgravell/protobuf-net/pull/287
please review. @mgravell 
I've improved the code for ProtoInherit please help me to review https://github.com/mgravell/protobuf-net/compare/master...chrishaly:master, if it's ok I will create a pull request. Or else please give me some advise.. * the ProtoInherit is used on SubType, which treat BaseType as a (virtual) Field
* Field number of BaseType suggest to be 1, in .NET just support single inheritace
* just keep in concrete class fieldNumber of ProtoInherit not duplicate with fields & ProtoInclude's fieldNumber, no need to think about field number in BaseType or it's SubType.
