oneof is not sutable for ProtoInherit.. protobuf usually used to transport data from end to end, the data is indistinguishable whole. and except bytes content of protobuf, there usually have some other filed to mark what's the type is. such as in RPC extra data at least function name will represent, function name awared the request type is also awared.
the actual packet may be like {funcationName: "GetProduct", RequestContent: "bytes data"}.
if your ProtoInclude we still should know the exact concrete type. Even if it's not need to know the exact concrete type type base type must aware, so we transported the base type why not directly transport the exact type.
So I think what the exact type is not a problem.
The scenario of ProtoInherit such as: 
base type is provider by other team, we are don't have permission to modify them.
what's we provided is class library there's no controllable entry to do AddSubType to user's TypeModel.
when write the concrete child type just mark it's base type not need to do some extra configuration.
ProtoInherit used on concrete type what is transparent to it's base type. if the concrete type will be remove just delete the class file, no need to do extra work.
